Line a 5- to 6-quart slow cooker with a Reynolds(R) Slow Cooker Liner. Place 2 packages of the corn in a blender with the cream or milk. Cover and blend until smooth. Transfer to prepared slow cooker. Stir remaining corn, onion, Parmesan cheese, butter, and salt into the corn mixture in cooker. Stir gently with a rubber spatula to combine. Cover and cook for 2 hours on high or for 4 hours on low. Transfer to a serving dish. Sprinkle with Monterey Jack cheese, bacon, tomato, and basil.